<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-18T03:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-18T03:30:00-05:00" n="259" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/2155: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Officer in Charge at New Delhi</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-18T15:00:00+06:30">October
                                    18, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 18—11:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>757. The Viceroy in a farewell off the record interview with an Indian
                            journalist whom he has known for past 15 years, stated it was his firm
                            conviction that British must continue rule India for another 50 years.
                            It would take at least that long, he said, for Indians to learn to
                            govern themselves.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Merrell</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>